gainst the backdrop of his complex relationship with the Egyptian state, the religious establishment, and the French government, Hussam R. Ahmed reveals modern Egypt's cultural influence in the Arab and Islamic world within the various structural changes and political processes of the parliamentary period. Ahmed offers both a history of modern state formation, revealing how the Egyptian state came to hold such a strong grip over culture and education—and a compelling examination of the life of the country's most renowned intellectual.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aEducation and statezEgyptxHistoryy20th century. 0aEducation ministerszEgyptvBiography. 0aIntellectualszEgyptvBiography. 0aIntellectualszEgypt. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh  aTaha Hussein.  aadab.  acultural history.  ademocracy.  ahumanism.  ainstitutional history.  anahda.  aparliamentary Egypt.  asocial history.  auniversity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107391450 cprintz978150361534240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362796340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503627963423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503627963/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075408-7 